Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs Hicks and London out, Allen and Conklin dressing for MSU Joe Rexrode, Detroit Free Press 3:24 p.m. EDT October 17, 2015 Michigan State Spartans cornerback Darian Hicks (Photo: Andrew Weber-USA TODAY Sports) 
Two more Michigan State starters are out for today's game after suffering injuries last week, cornerback Darian Hicks (head) and running back Madre London (leg) both aren't dressing for the No. 7 Spartans (6-0, 2-0 Big Ten). 
But center Jack Allen, who left last week's 31-24 win at Rutgers late with a right ankle injury, is dressing, as is starting left tackle Jack Conklin. Conklin hasn't played since suffering a knee injury Sept. 26 against Central Michigan. 
MSU still hasn't announced if Allen and Conklin are actually available to play, and no starting lineup has been issued yet. In pre-game warmups, backup center Brian Allen was snapping to Connor Cook, and Jack Allen was not on the field. 
Also today, MSU senior defensive end Shilique Calhoun is switching from his normal No. 89 to No. 43 to honor teammate Ed Davis. Davis, a senior linebacker, is missing the season after suffering a knee injury in camp. Read or Share this story: http://on.lsj.com/1ROzoM0 TOP VIDEOS
